                <note rend="inline" type="source">600.119/2009b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="67" xml:id="d704fn67">The same, on same date, to Embassies
                        in France (for McFadden, No. 587, for Taylor) and in Italy (for Stewart, No.
                        62).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-13">January 13,
                            1919</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For Sheldon [from War Trade Board]: No. 2050. Applications for export licenses to
                    Allied countries are no longer being referred to the Allied Missions here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
